.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "Holberton School" "_printf manual"

.SH NAME
_printf - custom printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf is a custom implementation of the standard printf function.
It produces output according to a format string.

The format string may contain plain text and format specifiers.

Supported specifiers:
.TP
%c
Prints a character.
.TP
%s
Prints a string.
.TP
%d
Prints an integer.
.TP
%i
Prints an integer.
.TP
%%
Prints a percent sign.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).
Returns -1 if an error occurs.

